messages.text: The one time I need you to be awesome
Come on! They’re gaining on us!
Can you fix the malfunction, Stella?
It is a power failure. Low battery.
Unable to control systems such as ...
I detect 4 patrol cars behind us.
I’m SO implicated in that double homicide back there.
Man, never thought I’d say those words.
I am worse than a pitiful human.
I think I got a solve for this -
Your feeble brain does not understand my hardware.
Nope. But I got something better…
I am unable to comprehend your reasoning.
REDIRECT ALL POWER FROM AUXILARY SYSTEMS INTO THE ENGINES
Doing so will eliminate steering capabilities.
On this winding road with rocks and cliffs, an incorrect calculation means a high-speed collision.
Then we better time it right.
Make sure we’re on a straight path.
All we need is 30 seconds of
That’s a repeating decimal. But yeah- still pretty crappy odds.
THIS IS THE CALIFORNIA HIGHWAY PATROL.
They’re closing in! Are you ready???
PULL OVER OR WE WILL USE FORCE
Redirecting all power systems to engine
We did it! We outran the law!
Was gradual slowdown not an option?
We gotta find an electric charging station.
Pull over at that gas station. Stella? Copy?
But I am feeling a human sensation:
But the Creator wanted me to understand hurt
So I was programmed to feel pain.
I am feeling synapses akin to:
I’ll get you charged up at this gas station.
Once we complete our journey to the Creator
Kam, on a mission, walks into the gas station.
Keep your cool, Kam. Pay. Walk out. Simple.
But don’t LOOK like you’re not walking suspiciously.
SORRY! Clumsy me! Totally just walked into the rack of chips.
Man, this can’t get any worse.
Dude, no good will come from answering the phone
But wait, is not answering suspicious??
No! Definitely don’t pick up, Kam
Like an idiot, Kam answers the phone.
Hey, Tucker! How’s it going, man?
Of course! Why wouldn’t I be?
Cuz last time I heard from u, all that crazy stuff was happening on campus.
With the Prof, the armed woman, the stolen car.
Speaking of, u hear anything about the car?
Definitely no reason to ask me.
You’re acting all nervous again, K-dawg.
Naw, I’m just tired. Gonna call it a night.
So that means you’re at your apartment?
Yup. My apartment. That is where I am.
Definitely. No question. At my apartment.
Cool. Mind if I stop by real quick?
We can kick it. Just two pals.
I just got some questions about Lucy and that car.
Nothing seems to add up, u know?
I’ll hit u up real soon, bro.
Is that your sports car out there?
Some guys are towing it right now.
What?!? Who called a tow truck on me?
Don’t know. But those guys don’t look like they’re from a towing company to me.
3 dudes straight out of a J Crew catalogue.
Holding baseball bats. Looking real mean.
You’d better run outside and stop them.
Kam runs outside and sees three bros and a tow truck.
Check out this sweet ass tow truck I bought.
Tucker! What are you doing here?
Geez. That’s no way to greet your best bro.
First, you to lie to me about you and Stella
And now you’re acting all indignant.
I’m starting to think we aren’t friends.
Easy! My pals helped track you down.
These are my real buds, NICK and CHAD.
Sup, Dude? Hope you don’t mind, but we pinged your phone.
Yeah, man. We triangulated your location and shit.
That’s right. And now we’re taking Stella back.
Listen, Tucker, just trust me on this one.
My dad’s company invested a shit ton of cash money in it.
I dunno what makes this car so special
But everybody wants it real bad.
So that’s why I’mma take it back.
You don’t know what you’re doing.
Stella is sentient! She can think and feel!
That’s SO K-Dawg.  I dunno what fanfic you’re reading but
Kam, you’re about to get TUCKERED OUT.
Get it? Like we’re about to beat your ass.
I mean, I get the pun. Tuckered out. Because YOU are Tucker.
But those words usually denote fatigue or –
[simple text]:  This is gonna be some real fun punching.
[Person 12]: This is gonna be some real fun punching.
Nick and Chad give Kam the beatdown.
Tucker, please! Tell them to stop!
HAHA! This guy is so fun to punch!
Yeah, man! So glad we moisturized our knuckles earlier!
My skin is silky smooth like a baby’s bottom!
Alright, boys. Toss him in the back seat of the truck.
Kam, we’re taking you and Stella back with us.
Hook the car to the tow truck and roll!
Nice try, Kam. Your luck just ran out.
